INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(27660, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know why you are here, $N. Your reasons sing within your fluids.$B$BI know about the dead dwarf forgesmith polluting my lake. If you want to find out what his corpse remembers, you must earn it.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27701, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Isn\'t she beautiful? So graceful.$B$BI hope she gets her fill of revenge and then some.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27696, 396, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s a very sharp axe. It\'ll do the job, but if I\'m any judge of weaponry, that\'s not what Cho\'gall\'s after.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27689, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That takes care of most of their leaders outside of the Bastion of Twilight. Not bad work, $N. Not bad at all.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27662, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'d I tell you? Elementals aren\'t so bad after all, eh?', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27658, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$N! I\'m glad you\'re here.$B$BOf course, I\'m more than willing to help you in any way that I can.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27655, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Feels good to get a little blood on your hands, doesn\'t it? Especially when that blood belongs to such self-deluded fools.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27653, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What do you think I should do with all of these? Maybe I\'ll melt them down and have the metal imbued into a new dagger that I can thrust into Cho\'gall\'s chest.$B$BThink there\'s time for that?', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27638, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where are the Kor\'kron?', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27503, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This can\'t be good!', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27501, 11, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The noble lady grins wickedly.>$B$BThat\'s quite a gruesome trophy collection you have there. I would have believed you if you had simply said they were dead, though I do appreciate the extra effort. Thank you for having the foresight to take care of them.$B$BThe Twilight Gate will soon be ours. Time to move up to the Twilight Citadel.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27499, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The horns have been sounded.  Crushblow should launch their attack at any moment.$B$BNow there\'s only one thing left to take care of.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27495, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Success!', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27491, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That must have been exciting.$B$BDespite any losses that the Kor\'kron may have incurred along the way, no one will be able to doubt their effectiveness, nor that of Garona. And with you in the mix, it\'s only a matter of time before victory is ours.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27493, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And here I thought that today couldn\'t get any better.$B$BI enjoy being wrong, occasionally.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(27497, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must say that I rather enjoyed the sight of their buildings being hit.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28249, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, $n. We\'re in the process of preparing the attack now.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28247, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You killed Obsidia within her own lair? Impressive, $r. I\'m sorry that I could not be there.$B$BYou\'re true to your word, and you most certainly have the bite to back your bellow. Thank you.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28176, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lirastraza sent me ahead to the lair, suspecting the black dragon we are seeking may still be here. Judging by the hatchlings, it seems she was not mistaken.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28173, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You seem to have made use of the disturbing implements with ease.$B$BI take solace in knowing that some tools of evil can ultimately still lead to safeguarding life. Nothing is without purpose.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28191, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve proven a great ally. I would have never expected such upon our first meeting.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28175, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve started a wonderful thing this day, amidst all of this blood shed.$B$BIt may take many years, but this ravaged land will be restored. It will be beautiful again.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28171, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems you are still with us. I\'m somewhat appreciative of that.$B$BThank you.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28758, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks to your quick action, the Dragon Queen still lives. She is being brought back to Wyrmrest to recover.$B$BBut the battle wasn\'t a complete failure. Deathwing was gravely wounded. I suspect he will go into hiding to recuperate. Alexstrasza has bought us time to strike!', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28712, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello again, $r. I hear you were instrumental in our push toward Grim Batol - thank you!$B$BAlexstrasza has sanctified this ground in the hopes of luring Deathwing here. She\'ll perform a ceremony to lure him out... and then destroy him within this sacred circle.$B$BLet\'s hope her plan works.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28093, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The gate is clear. Once your people finish clearing the canyon, we will speak to your leaders about the next move.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28092, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Works like a charm, every time.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28094, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We make it look easy.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28097, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The canyon is well fortified, but the distraction that the dragons are providing should be enough to allow us to break through.', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28090, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good going.$B$BDoesn\'t look like much, does it?', 15595), -- -Unknown-
(28091, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Now we can start pushing our ground forces up towards Grim Batol.', 15595); -- -Unknown-
